1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:32,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.xyz Support Admin)

2
00:00:39,215 --> 00:00:40,545
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

3
00:00:40,545 --> 00:00:41,975
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:01:41,035 --> 00:01:42,035
You did great.

5
00:02:10,535 --> 00:02:12,035
The reason I asked to meet...

6
00:02:12,805 --> 00:02:16,145
As you know, I was looking after
Jin Ju for a few years.

7
00:02:16,905 --> 00:02:19,315
I think we should hold
her 49th-day memorial service.

8
00:02:20,345 --> 00:02:22,715
- She's not dead.
- But there are no signs of her...

9
00:02:22,715 --> 00:02:24,185
You think I don't know my own kid?

10
00:02:24,445 --> 00:02:27,315
How would he know?
He never even raised her.

11
00:02:28,355 --> 00:02:30,655
She's not the type to throw her life away.

12
00:02:30,655 --> 00:02:31,925
She's putting on an act.

13
00:02:32,025 --> 00:02:34,395
Would you write a suicide note
just as an act, sir?

14
00:02:34,655 --> 00:02:36,965
Her eyes were sparkling.

15
00:02:37,095 --> 00:02:38,525
With eyes like that,

16
00:02:39,365 --> 00:02:40,765
she wouldn't take her own life.

17
00:02:42,265 --> 00:02:43,835
Is he a face reader now?

18
00:02:46,335 --> 00:02:47,375
You even brought cake?

19
00:02:55,715 --> 00:02:57,485
Where'd you get this cake? It's amazing.

20
00:02:57,485 --> 00:02:58,545
I'm not telling.

21
00:02:58,955 --> 00:03:00,215
Just let me know when you're craving it.

22
00:03:00,215 --> 00:03:01,655
What if I crave it every day?

23
00:03:02,015 --> 00:03:03,255
I'll bring it to you every day.

24
00:03:03,325 --> 00:03:04,685
Do you have so much time on your hands?

25
00:03:04,755 --> 00:03:06,825
I have Manager Yoon
and Mr. Kim, the driver.

26
00:03:10,095 --> 00:03:11,425
It's time to let go of Jin Ju.

27
00:03:13,635 --> 00:03:16,235
In the end,
everyone goes their separate ways.

28
00:03:17,305 --> 00:03:20,675
Look at me.
I'm doing just fine without my parents.

29
00:03:26,215 --> 00:03:27,815
Pickles, did you hear that?

30
00:03:28,075 --> 00:03:29,745
We'll take good care of you.

31
00:03:31,185 --> 00:03:32,315
With love.

32
00:03:32,985 --> 00:03:36,155
I can't believe I have my own dog.

33
00:03:37,355 --> 00:03:38,525
Thanks, Yong Joong.

34
00:03:39,125 --> 00:03:41,055
You're the one who made me want a dog.

35
00:03:41,195 --> 00:03:42,465
I wasn't really interested before.

36
00:03:42,795 --> 00:03:44,825
Just let me know
if it ever becomes a bother.

37
00:03:45,665 --> 00:03:47,835
Once I get my heart set on something,
I don't change my mind.

38
00:03:48,665 --> 00:03:50,465
I'm not sure if that's good or bad.

39
00:03:51,605 --> 00:03:55,275
I guess his feelings for Momo
won't change either.

40
00:03:58,105 --> 00:03:59,115
Is that a bad thing?

41
00:04:01,475 --> 00:04:02,485
I don't know.

42
00:04:03,315 --> 00:04:04,615
So you think it's one of my flaws.

43
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:09,555
Nobody's perfect.

44
00:04:11,955 --> 00:04:14,555
What are my flaws?
I'll fix them if you tell me.

45
00:04:14,695 --> 00:04:16,065
I've never thought about it.

46
00:04:17,395 --> 00:04:19,495
I don't think you have any. None at all.

47
00:04:20,795 --> 00:04:23,435
But aren't flaws what make us human?

48
00:04:24,035 --> 00:04:27,375
Are you saying I'm human,
or that you aren't?

49
00:04:27,805 --> 00:04:28,805
Interpret it how you want.

50
00:04:30,245 --> 00:04:33,845
Well, if I'm the one who's human,
that means I have flaws you can point out.

51
00:04:36,015 --> 00:04:37,985
So do you consider yourself not human?

52
00:04:38,515 --> 00:04:41,415
To be honest, there are times
I feel less than human.

53
00:04:43,555 --> 00:04:45,625
I had to live that way to get by.

54
00:04:46,355 --> 00:04:48,955
Nothing ever came easy for me.

55
00:04:49,825 --> 00:04:51,295
Like cracking a whip on my own soul?

56
00:04:52,095 --> 00:04:54,265
I guess I was always very hard on myself.

57
00:04:54,595 --> 00:04:56,465
That doesn't make you less human.

58
00:04:57,065 --> 00:04:58,905
It's not like you were a burden to others.

59
00:05:00,075 --> 00:05:01,935
You just did your absolute best.

60
00:05:02,705 --> 00:05:04,675
From now on,
you should take care of yourself, too.

61
00:05:07,245 --> 00:05:08,545
I know what you mean.

62
00:05:08,815 --> 00:05:10,315
You deserve love...

63
00:05:10,915 --> 00:05:13,315
and recognition, my little lady.

64
00:07:08,895 --> 00:07:11,705
- Would you like an Americano?
- I've already had several cups.

65
00:07:11,765 --> 00:07:15,235
How about a small 49th-day memorial
for Jin Ju, just among ourselves?

66
00:07:22,115 --> 00:07:23,815
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

67
00:07:23,885 --> 00:07:25,085
Goodbye.

68
00:07:46,735 --> 00:07:49,705
Her "father" won't hold the service,
claiming she's alive.

69
00:07:49,775 --> 00:07:50,845
Can you believe it?

70
00:07:50,905 --> 00:07:52,615
And the police have already
closed the case.

71
00:07:53,545 --> 00:07:55,445
He must not want to believe it.

72
00:07:57,845 --> 00:07:59,485
Should we just do it
with her memorial tablet?

73
00:08:00,955 --> 00:08:03,425
We should probably have
something she wore, though.

74
00:08:05,855 --> 00:08:07,295
I wonder if Momo will come.

75
00:08:42,295 --> 00:08:44,295
(Ba Ra)

76
00:08:49,835 --> 00:08:50,835
Hey, Ba Ra.

77
00:08:53,705 --> 00:08:55,875
- Is this a good time to talk?
- Of course.

78
00:08:56,105 --> 00:08:58,275
I talked it over with James,

79
00:08:59,375 --> 00:09:02,045
and we're holding a 49th-day memorial
for Jin Ju.

80
00:09:02,585 --> 00:09:03,885
I was calling to see if you could come.

81
00:09:04,915 --> 00:09:06,185
My 49th-day memorial?

82
00:09:09,425 --> 00:09:10,825
But no pressure if you don't want to.

83
00:09:11,755 --> 00:09:12,755
When is it?

84
00:09:12,755 --> 00:09:14,825
Saturday, 2 p.m. at Eunkyungsa Temple.

85
00:09:16,265 --> 00:09:18,225
Jin Ju was always so good to you.

86
00:09:19,865 --> 00:09:20,865
She really was.

87
00:09:23,165 --> 00:09:25,865
- The temple in Gapyeong?
- That's the one.

88
00:09:26,075 --> 00:09:27,235
I'll drive you.

89
00:09:29,075 --> 00:09:30,205
So you're coming?

90
00:09:30,845 --> 00:09:31,845
Yes.

91
00:09:32,575 --> 00:09:33,845
It's not like she was just anybody.

92
00:09:37,785 --> 00:09:39,355
We should leave by noon, then.

93
00:09:40,955 --> 00:09:41,955
Got it.

94
00:09:42,725 --> 00:09:43,725
Thanks.

95
00:09:44,655 --> 00:09:45,655
Don't mention it.

96
00:09:54,735 --> 00:09:57,565
The articles are all over the news sites.
Have you seen them?

97
00:09:57,835 --> 00:10:00,305
Yes. The trolls are having a field day.

98
00:10:00,675 --> 00:10:03,505
I have to write one too. My editors...

99
00:10:03,505 --> 00:10:05,375
Write whatever you want. It's okay.

100
00:10:05,705 --> 00:10:07,175
Go ahead and make it even harsher.

101
00:10:08,775 --> 00:10:11,085
I know everything there is to know
about Momo.

102
00:10:29,065 --> 00:10:30,235
Why so flustered?

103
00:10:31,765 --> 00:10:33,075
We were engaged, you know.

104
00:10:33,535 --> 00:10:36,075
That was a difficult surgery,
so pull yourself together.

105
00:10:38,045 --> 00:10:39,045
Yes.

106
00:10:39,675 --> 00:10:41,175
And stop walking on eggshells around me.

107
00:10:43,245 --> 00:10:44,245
Okay.

108
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:33,535
Open.

109
00:11:38,605 --> 00:11:39,605
Look.

110
00:12:10,465 --> 00:12:11,465
Deity,

111
00:12:12,465 --> 00:12:13,905
is this really happening?

112
00:12:24,985 --> 00:12:25,985
Yong Joong.

113
00:12:27,055 --> 00:12:28,055
I came to pick you up.

114
00:12:28,985 --> 00:12:30,185
Pickles!

115
00:12:32,995 --> 00:12:34,055
You're so cute.

116
00:12:34,425 --> 00:12:36,425
That's heavy.
Your shoulders are going to get lopsided.

117
00:12:36,765 --> 00:12:38,165
You can take my other car today.

118
00:12:38,895 --> 00:12:40,395
You're just asking for rumors.

119
00:12:40,465 --> 00:12:41,635
Tell them you found a sugar daddy.

120
00:12:42,465 --> 00:12:44,535
I'll walk him a bit. You go on up.

121
00:12:44,905 --> 00:12:47,275
- Why?
- Because that's heavy and in the way.

122
00:12:48,405 --> 00:12:49,405
Right.

123
00:12:50,145 --> 00:12:51,175
Let's go.

124
00:12:53,245 --> 00:12:57,045
They say dogs take after their owners,
so who do you think is his owner?

125
00:12:57,415 --> 00:12:59,485
Should we try it? See who he comes to?

126
00:12:59,785 --> 00:13:01,455
No, don't put him on the spot.

127
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:05,885
I might have been hurt
if you'd said hi to Pickles first.

128
00:13:06,055 --> 00:13:08,955
Come on, you're not that petty.

129
00:13:09,595 --> 00:13:11,895
I'd be hurt. It's not about being petty.

130
00:13:12,595 --> 00:13:15,565
Your heart is as big as the ocean.

131
00:13:16,565 --> 00:13:17,965
Spoken like a true reporter.

132
00:13:18,735 --> 00:13:20,975
Most people in Gen MZ wouldn't even know
that expression.

133
00:13:21,175 --> 00:13:22,735
Am I laying it on too thick today?

134
00:13:23,345 --> 00:13:24,545
You're always laying it on thick.

135
00:13:26,915 --> 00:13:27,915
Yong Joong.

136
00:13:31,445 --> 00:13:32,445
What did you do?

137
00:13:43,025 --> 00:13:44,425
This night

138
00:13:45,295 --> 00:13:50,565
I will send the fireflies of that day

139
00:13:51,405 --> 00:13:54,205
Near your

140
00:13:55,275 --> 00:13:59,545
Window

141
00:13:59,915 --> 00:14:02,985
Pane

142
00:14:10,755 --> 00:14:12,925
I don't think I'll ever forget tonight.

143
00:14:15,225 --> 00:14:20,165
It means

144
00:14:20,865 --> 00:14:23,565
I love you

145
00:14:26,105 --> 00:14:30,045
I remember

146
00:14:30,805 --> 00:14:36,145
When we first met

147
00:14:37,445 --> 00:14:38,845
And so

148
00:14:39,515 --> 00:14:45,485
Whenever I close my eyes

149
00:14:50,295 --> 00:14:54,895
I go to the most

150
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:57,605
Distant place

151
00:15:02,235 --> 00:15:04,145
I guess I'll have to make lots of memories
with you.

152
00:15:07,045 --> 00:15:09,745
But you can't force memories.
That doesn't count.

153
00:15:10,085 --> 00:15:11,315
It wouldn't be forced.

154
00:15:11,785 --> 00:15:14,185
Were you a good son? Or a rebel?

155
00:15:15,985 --> 00:15:16,985
A bit of both?

156
00:15:21,495 --> 00:15:24,625
Well, to me, you were the sweetest guy
in the world.

157
00:15:26,665 --> 00:15:27,695
I love you.

158
00:15:38,175 --> 00:15:41,545
Pickles.
She just blew off my "I love you."

159
00:15:42,245 --> 00:15:44,345
I chewed it into tiny pieces
and swallowed.

160
00:15:45,645 --> 00:15:47,385
I'm filled to the brim with love.

161
00:15:48,615 --> 00:15:52,025
If I say even one word,
I'm afraid some of it might spill out.

162
00:15:57,425 --> 00:16:00,135
- Why the sigh?
- This must be how dads feel.

163
00:16:01,865 --> 00:16:03,735
You really haven't dated anyone
all this time, have you?

164
00:16:04,205 --> 00:16:07,275
If you had, some other guy would be
next to you right now, not me.

165
00:16:09,905 --> 00:16:12,005
No guy in his right mind
could ever leave you.

166
00:16:13,515 --> 00:16:14,845
That kind of sounds like an insult.

167
00:16:15,815 --> 00:16:18,385
Don't you go flirting with anyone but me.

168
00:16:27,995 --> 00:16:29,655
Am I flirting? Is that what I'm doing?

169
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:34,365
- No.
- You said you didn't see me as a woman.

170
00:16:34,795 --> 00:16:35,895
You said I was your little sister.

171
00:16:36,335 --> 00:16:37,765
Is that something you'd say
to your little sister?

172
00:16:39,065 --> 00:16:41,575
- That's not what I meant.
- What about me blowing off your love?

173
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:44,145
And calling me a flirt
just for winking at you?

174
00:16:44,775 --> 00:16:46,345
To me, it's a wink,

175
00:16:46,775 --> 00:16:48,945
but other guys might see it
as you flirting.

176
00:16:52,185 --> 00:16:53,855
Not everyone's as innocent as me,
you know.

177
00:16:54,915 --> 00:16:57,325
Right, you're just overflowing
with purity.

178
00:16:57,785 --> 00:17:00,455
I've had my fill of pure, innocent love,
thanks.

179
00:17:00,795 --> 00:17:02,555
So go pour it all out on Momo
to your heart's content.

180
00:17:10,005 --> 00:17:11,005
Geum Ba Ra.

181
00:17:15,035 --> 00:17:16,235
Are you really that mad?

182
00:17:17,945 --> 00:17:20,945
Sorry. I didn't grow up with sisters,
so I don't really get it.

183
00:17:21,345 --> 00:17:23,045
Didn't you say you dated older girls
in high school?

184
00:17:23,345 --> 00:17:25,085
- Twice.
- And Momo?

185
00:17:26,285 --> 00:17:27,855
It's just a one-sided crush.

186
00:17:30,025 --> 00:17:31,585
At last year's Appreciation Night,

187
00:17:32,685 --> 00:17:34,495
was Momo so captivating...

188
00:17:35,755 --> 00:17:37,295
that you're still not over her?

189
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:40,065
What was so great about her?

190
00:17:41,435 --> 00:17:42,435
That she's pretty?

191
00:17:43,365 --> 00:17:44,405
Or a good dancer?

192
00:17:45,365 --> 00:17:46,365
I don't know,

193
00:17:48,175 --> 00:17:49,475
it was like an electric shock.

194
00:17:51,375 --> 00:17:52,375
Like a...

195
00:17:54,845 --> 00:17:56,015
jolt.

196
00:17:57,385 --> 00:17:58,385
In your heart?

197
00:17:59,645 --> 00:18:00,655
In your body?

198
00:18:01,755 --> 00:18:03,055
If I'd had no self-control,

199
00:18:05,755 --> 00:18:06,825
I would have held her.

200
00:18:08,455 --> 00:18:10,025
Or grabbed her hand and ran off with her.

201
00:18:11,265 --> 00:18:12,395
It was that intense?

202
00:18:13,835 --> 00:18:15,335
I can't hide anything from you.

203
00:18:16,635 --> 00:18:17,905
When I wake up in the morning,

204
00:18:19,505 --> 00:18:21,105
I wake up thinking of Momo.

205
00:18:22,835 --> 00:18:23,875
It's the same when I go to sleep.

206
00:18:26,515 --> 00:18:28,375
Then you should just get it
off your chest.

207
00:18:28,975 --> 00:18:31,745
- You want me to be a scumbag to Ju Shin?
- They're not married yet.

208
00:18:31,815 --> 00:18:33,815
I can't just live my life
based on my own feelings.

209
00:18:34,315 --> 00:18:36,215
Imagine if everyone did that.
What would the world come to?

210
00:18:36,855 --> 00:18:38,685
It'd be chaos, with no morality.

211
00:18:38,825 --> 00:18:39,955
But later,

212
00:18:42,395 --> 00:18:44,325
if, by some chance,
she and Ju Shin break up,

213
00:18:46,095 --> 00:18:47,095
what then?

214
00:18:51,935 --> 00:18:53,205
Then, I'd be honest.

215
00:18:55,475 --> 00:18:56,575
Without a second thought?

216
00:18:56,775 --> 00:18:57,875
What else would matter?

217
00:18:59,745 --> 00:19:00,845
Liking someone...

218
00:19:01,675 --> 00:19:03,245
doesn't require reasons or conditions.

219
00:19:05,915 --> 00:19:07,185
If only the one...

220
00:19:08,515 --> 00:19:09,685
he was talking about were me...

221
00:19:11,525 --> 00:19:12,585
Hey, he's pooping.

222
00:19:37,485 --> 00:19:38,585
Go home and stay there.

223
00:19:40,355 --> 00:19:42,985
The Cheongdam-dong house.
Don't even go near Hyeonmi-dong.

224
00:19:45,185 --> 00:19:46,185
Okay.

225
00:19:50,225 --> 00:19:52,025
As of now, Kim Jin Ju no longer exists.

226
00:19:52,895 --> 00:19:54,635
Be extra careful
when you're around Geum Ba Ra.

227
00:19:55,535 --> 00:19:57,665
Her job is one thing,
but she's also naturally perceptive.

228
00:19:58,705 --> 00:19:59,705
You're right.

229
00:20:00,575 --> 00:20:02,675
I just don't think
we should jump right into it now.

230
00:20:03,175 --> 00:20:04,645
You'd need to be mentally prepared.

231
00:20:24,025 --> 00:20:27,095
From now on,
I'm going to love you, too, Holy Father.

232
00:20:48,785 --> 00:20:51,125
- Hello?
- This is Paul Kim.

233
00:20:51,525 --> 00:20:52,655
About my piece from the other day...

234
00:20:52,655 --> 00:20:54,055
Yes, Mr. Kim.

235
00:20:54,495 --> 00:20:57,395
I put it up at my place,
and it looks amazing.

236
00:20:57,465 --> 00:20:59,765
I'm glad.
Listen, the reason I'm calling is...

237
00:20:59,995 --> 00:21:04,035
I saw the news a while back
about Kim Jin Ju going missing...

238
00:21:04,165 --> 00:21:06,135
You know Kim Jin Ju?

239
00:21:06,135 --> 00:21:08,705
I do. It's a bit of a long story.

240
00:21:08,935 --> 00:21:11,175
Your studio's in Yangpyeong, right?

241
00:21:11,175 --> 00:21:12,675
I'm in Seoul at the moment.

242
00:21:13,045 --> 00:21:15,845
Where in Seoul?
Why don't you come over to my place?

243
00:21:16,275 --> 00:21:17,345
Would that be okay?

244
00:21:17,585 --> 00:21:20,555
Of course.
You can see your piece on display.

245
00:21:22,015 --> 00:21:23,685
Goodness. So?

246
00:21:24,055 --> 00:21:26,995
We did a DNA test, and we weren't a match.

247
00:21:27,095 --> 00:21:31,125
I have a long story myself.
Kim Jin Ju's biological father showed up.

248
00:21:32,295 --> 00:21:34,265
- Really?
- Yes.

249
00:21:34,595 --> 00:21:37,935
The news didn't get into the specifics,

250
00:21:38,505 --> 00:21:40,905
but I think she did what she did
because of her biological father.

251
00:21:45,975 --> 00:21:47,515
(Kim Jin Ju 0342)

252
00:21:52,815 --> 00:21:53,815
(Kim Jin Ju 0342)

253
00:21:57,785 --> 00:21:59,625
I guess her door code changed.

254
00:21:59,755 --> 00:22:01,425
So you're running an errand
for my daughter?

255
00:22:01,655 --> 00:22:02,725
To pick up her things?

256
00:22:02,995 --> 00:22:05,295
No. Her 49th-day memorial service
is the day after tomorrow,

257
00:22:05,365 --> 00:22:06,695
and I need to get an outfit of hers.

258
00:22:08,235 --> 00:22:09,735
Where are you holding the service?

259
00:22:10,035 --> 00:22:11,465
At Eunkyungsa Temple in Gapyeong.

260
00:22:12,705 --> 00:22:13,875
In any case,

261
00:22:14,605 --> 00:22:16,475
this whole thing feels like a setup...

262
00:22:16,705 --> 00:22:18,475
I think you need to accept it.

263
00:22:18,475 --> 00:22:20,215
- I know it's hard to believe...
- What is there to accept?

264
00:22:22,475 --> 00:22:23,785
You tell my daughter...

265
00:22:24,345 --> 00:22:26,115
that I'm going to find her no matter what.

266
00:22:26,915 --> 00:22:28,215
Sir, I need her outfit...

267
00:22:44,805 --> 00:22:47,335
I'm in the spot where Momo used to sit.

268
00:22:57,445 --> 00:22:58,685
(Jaeil Apartments)

269
00:23:21,235 --> 00:23:22,335
You look so elegant.

270
00:23:31,185 --> 00:23:32,545
I went to get an outfit of hers,

271
00:23:32,815 --> 00:23:35,055
but I couldn't even enter
because of Jin Ju's dad.

272
00:23:35,785 --> 00:23:36,855
He's actually living there?

273
00:23:37,155 --> 00:23:38,155
Yes.

274
00:23:38,425 --> 00:23:40,955
He even had a DNA test done.
What are we supposed to say?

275
00:23:41,225 --> 00:23:42,655
Technically, it's his daughter's house.

276
00:23:43,025 --> 00:23:44,395
How did he get a DNA test?

277
00:23:44,695 --> 00:23:45,725
Without her even being there?

278
00:23:45,725 --> 00:23:47,265
He used Jin Ju's toothbrush.

279
00:23:47,535 --> 00:23:48,735
They said it was a perfect match.

280
00:23:49,335 --> 00:23:51,365
James confirmed everything too.

281
00:24:01,015 --> 00:24:02,645
Jin Ju said that
when the weather was nice,

282
00:24:02,915 --> 00:24:04,945
she wanted to go to an arboretum.

283
00:24:06,855 --> 00:24:07,885
I just can't believe it.

284
00:24:08,815 --> 00:24:10,755
She had such a strong will to live.

285
00:24:13,695 --> 00:24:14,695
"Will to live?"

286
00:24:16,225 --> 00:24:18,025
You know how many things she wanted to do.

287
00:24:19,865 --> 00:24:22,295
If you knew her so well,
why were you so cold to her?

288
00:24:23,435 --> 00:24:25,435
- Coffee.
- Okay.

289
00:24:26,305 --> 00:24:28,105
Do we have to leave money when we bow?

290
00:24:28,105 --> 00:24:30,275
I think so. I brought some just in case.

291
00:24:30,345 --> 00:24:31,375
Feeling cheap?

292
00:24:32,475 --> 00:24:33,675
I don't have to go in, right?

293
00:24:34,615 --> 00:24:37,115
You worked with her for years,
and you won't even bow once?

294
00:24:50,425 --> 00:24:51,695
(Kim Jin Ju)

295
00:24:56,035 --> 00:24:57,505
Of all the pictures,
they had to use that one.

296
00:24:58,505 --> 00:24:59,535
So tacky.

297
00:25:08,275 --> 00:25:11,915
(Minjin Church)

298
00:25:14,315 --> 00:25:16,155
(God Loves You)

299
00:25:16,215 --> 00:25:17,955
(A Place of Dreams and Love)

300
00:25:18,025 --> 00:25:19,655
(Please be sure to write down
the name and date of birth)

301
00:25:19,725 --> 00:25:20,895
(Baby Box)

302
00:25:26,065 --> 00:25:28,435
Jin Ju, you've had this
since you were a baby.

303
00:25:46,885 --> 00:25:48,415
Hey.

304
00:25:49,115 --> 00:25:50,185
I said look.

305
00:27:37,295 --> 00:27:40,665
What was your connection to the deceased,
Momo?

306
00:27:41,065 --> 00:27:42,395
She was my stylist.

307
00:27:43,335 --> 00:27:45,305
The monk performing the rites
is very devout.

308
00:27:45,565 --> 00:27:47,275
I'm sure her spirit has passed
on peacefully.

309
00:27:47,735 --> 00:27:50,945
Master. Mr. Park is about to leave.

310
00:27:51,845 --> 00:27:52,845
Excuse me for a moment.

311
00:27:53,145 --> 00:27:54,145
Okay.

312
00:28:00,955 --> 00:28:02,085
Didn't you want to cry?

313
00:28:03,115 --> 00:28:04,485
You two grew up together at the orphanage.

314
00:28:06,955 --> 00:28:09,525
It still doesn't feel real to me either.

315
00:28:10,155 --> 00:28:11,865
The human heart is a funny thing.

316
00:28:12,265 --> 00:28:14,735
Since her biological father
keeps saying she isn't dead,

317
00:28:14,835 --> 00:28:16,935
and it's not like we saw a body,

318
00:28:17,565 --> 00:28:19,505
I feel like she's really alive somewhere.

319
00:28:20,005 --> 00:28:21,335
All signs suggest she fell into the ocean,

320
00:28:21,335 --> 00:28:22,675
so how are we supposed to confirm it?

321
00:28:24,045 --> 00:28:25,245
You're right.

322
00:28:25,705 --> 00:28:27,915
Anyway, it's a shame
to die in the prime of her life.

323
00:28:28,375 --> 00:28:30,515
It's like she never even had a chance
to fall in love.

324
00:28:31,045 --> 00:28:34,415
My love has begun with Director Shin.

325
00:28:39,485 --> 00:28:41,555
I found a Korean place nearby
with good reviews.

326
00:28:41,755 --> 00:28:42,895
Eat something before you go.

327
00:28:42,955 --> 00:28:44,065
I already have plans.

328
00:28:44,995 --> 00:28:48,195
A friend invited me to a housewarming,
so I said I was going with you.

329
00:28:49,835 --> 00:28:51,835
I contacted you because...

330
00:28:51,835 --> 00:28:53,735
Kim Jin Ju's business card
had Lim Company.

331
00:28:53,805 --> 00:28:55,675
I was very surprised too.

332
00:28:56,635 --> 00:28:58,975
I was really hoping she was my daughter.

333
00:28:59,145 --> 00:29:02,545
I see. What a strange fate...

334
00:29:02,945 --> 00:29:05,385
That's Korea for you.
Word just spread from one person...

335
00:29:05,515 --> 00:29:06,515
Are you leaving now?

336
00:29:07,045 --> 00:29:08,715
Yes. You need your rest.

337
00:29:08,855 --> 00:29:10,385
This is relaxing for me.

338
00:29:10,655 --> 00:29:12,325
Please call me whenever you are in Seoul.

339
00:29:12,455 --> 00:29:13,995
If you ever have a reason
to come to Yangpyeong...

340
00:29:17,865 --> 00:29:19,365
Will one be enough
for her spirit to find peace?

341
00:29:19,365 --> 00:29:22,335
A very devout monk performed the rite.

342
00:29:24,935 --> 00:29:26,265
Please, wait a little bit.

343
00:29:26,405 --> 00:29:27,875
Let me prepare something for you to eat.

344
00:29:27,935 --> 00:29:30,645
- No, there's a place nearby...
- There are no decent restaurants nearby.

345
00:29:31,745 --> 00:29:34,015
I'm a pretty decent cook myself.

346
00:29:35,475 --> 00:29:36,975
And for wine?

347
00:29:37,415 --> 00:29:38,415
Should we?

348
00:29:40,115 --> 00:29:41,215
Today calls for it.

349
00:29:41,615 --> 00:29:43,855
- We'll do the pairing.
- Very good.

350
00:29:45,785 --> 00:29:48,125
We could've just eaten with James,

351
00:29:48,195 --> 00:29:50,125
I wanted to talk, just the two of us.

352
00:29:51,025 --> 00:29:53,325
Honestly, Mr. Ha talks way too much.

353
00:29:53,935 --> 00:29:55,035
It's exhausting.

354
00:29:56,535 --> 00:29:59,205
I guess I'd gotten
really attached to Jin Ju.

355
00:29:59,635 --> 00:30:01,605
I just suddenly burst into tears.

356
00:30:02,475 --> 00:30:04,405
I've gotten weaker after my mom died.

357
00:30:07,005 --> 00:30:10,315
But I'm glad you pulled yourself together.

358
00:30:10,815 --> 00:30:13,415
I figured you'd want to be alone,
so I didn't contact you.

359
00:30:13,785 --> 00:30:16,215
But I was always worried about you.

360
00:30:18,455 --> 00:30:19,485
Yes.

361
00:30:21,595 --> 00:30:22,725
What's your annual salary?

362
00:30:24,025 --> 00:30:25,025
You make 50,000 dollars?

363
00:30:29,895 --> 00:30:33,335
After taxes and what I put into savings,
I'm not left with much.

364
00:30:33,875 --> 00:30:34,975
Help me out.

365
00:30:36,475 --> 00:30:37,475
Anything.

366
00:30:37,905 --> 00:30:39,775
Quit your job and come work for me.

367
00:30:42,375 --> 00:30:43,375
Yes?

368
00:30:44,085 --> 00:30:45,415
But you have Manager Oh.

369
00:30:45,845 --> 00:30:47,015
He's my business manager.

370
00:30:47,555 --> 00:30:50,355
I wish you'd be by my side.
I don't want anyone else.

371
00:30:52,025 --> 00:30:54,595
I'll double, no, triple your salary.

372
00:30:55,855 --> 00:30:57,495
It's not about the money...

373
00:30:57,495 --> 00:30:58,925
But you said you worried about me.

374
00:31:01,735 --> 00:31:02,935
Do you really need me, specifically?

375
00:31:03,965 --> 00:31:04,965
I do.

376
00:31:06,465 --> 00:31:09,605
I could quit acting in a heartbeat
if someone close to me wanted me to.

377
00:31:13,505 --> 00:31:16,975
- Let me think about it.
- That's just a nice way of saying no.

378
00:31:17,485 --> 00:31:18,485
Am I wrong?

379
00:31:20,015 --> 00:31:23,955
My seniors are finally recognizing me,
so just quitting out of the blue...

380
00:31:24,455 --> 00:31:26,285
And it's been my life goal
since I was a kid.

381
00:31:27,055 --> 00:31:28,695
It's a great career, I'll give you that.

382
00:31:28,955 --> 00:31:30,865
But even if you prove your talent,

383
00:31:30,865 --> 00:31:33,195
don’t you just end up
an old critic in the end?

384
00:31:33,895 --> 00:31:37,065
Isn't being a gallery director
better than that?

385
00:31:37,405 --> 00:31:38,535
Plus, there's no mandatory retirement age.

386
00:31:39,935 --> 00:31:43,775
Just help me recover for 2 to 3 years,
and then the gallery is all yours to run.

387
00:31:43,875 --> 00:31:46,675
You already know so many experts
in the art and cultural scene.

388
00:31:49,775 --> 00:31:51,415
She's running late.

389
00:32:01,225 --> 00:32:02,895
Don't think about it for too long.

390
00:32:03,895 --> 00:32:04,895
Okay.

391
00:32:05,295 --> 00:32:06,295
Bye.

392
00:32:07,365 --> 00:32:08,735
Thanks, anyway.

393
00:32:09,835 --> 00:32:11,805
I'll take that as a yes.

394
00:32:14,035 --> 00:32:15,235
I envy you.

395
00:32:16,275 --> 00:32:17,405
Why?

396
00:32:17,405 --> 00:32:19,345
Everyone loves you...

397
00:32:19,675 --> 00:32:21,245
And Yong Joong does too.

398
00:32:22,245 --> 00:32:24,185
Things aren't always what they seem
on the surface.

399
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:08,455
(Contacts: Geum Ba Ra)

400
00:33:10,825 --> 00:33:12,065
Hey.

401
00:33:12,395 --> 00:33:13,725
Pickles and I are at your front door.

402
00:33:14,035 --> 00:33:15,265
You're here?

403
00:33:15,965 --> 00:33:17,865
It's the same number code as your place.

404
00:33:20,435 --> 00:33:21,475
Have you been drinking?

405
00:33:23,475 --> 00:33:24,575
With Momo.

406
00:33:26,805 --> 00:33:29,975
It's hitting me now
since I'm home and can relax.

407
00:33:32,545 --> 00:33:33,715
Hey, Pickles.

408
00:33:37,855 --> 00:33:39,855
A last-minute workout was scheduled
for tomorrow.

409
00:33:41,125 --> 00:33:42,295
How much did you have?

410
00:33:42,725 --> 00:33:45,025
A wine pairing. Six glasses.

411
00:33:45,395 --> 00:33:46,525
Yes, that'll do it.

412
00:33:48,795 --> 00:33:49,795
And Momo?

413
00:33:50,295 --> 00:33:51,705
She's been fine.

414
00:33:56,275 --> 00:33:57,275
Drink this.

415
00:33:58,075 --> 00:33:59,145
Leave it.

416
00:34:07,755 --> 00:34:08,815
Is something bothering you?

417
00:34:09,455 --> 00:34:10,455
Feeling queasy?

418
00:34:10,885 --> 00:34:12,225
A little nauseous.

419
00:34:12,485 --> 00:34:15,125
Go. I don't want you to see me this way.

420
00:34:15,255 --> 00:34:16,325
Why not?

421
00:34:16,495 --> 00:34:17,895
You must have seen Momo.

422
00:34:18,795 --> 00:34:19,795
Yes.

423
00:34:20,295 --> 00:34:21,665
Should I ask her to come back?

424
00:34:21,665 --> 00:34:23,135
She can't have gone far.

425
00:34:24,065 --> 00:34:25,305
Go on inside and lie down properly.

426
00:34:41,855 --> 00:34:42,955
Do you want me to stay?

427
00:34:44,425 --> 00:34:46,625
- Why?
- I feel like I should be here for you.

428
00:34:47,185 --> 00:34:48,255
You seem like you're struggling.

429
00:34:49,825 --> 00:34:50,965
Is it that obvious?

430
00:34:51,525 --> 00:34:53,665
Whatever it is, you can tell me.

431
00:34:54,495 --> 00:34:55,535
I don't want to.

432
00:34:56,235 --> 00:34:57,705
I don't hide anything from you, you know.

433
00:34:58,565 --> 00:34:59,565
I'm a little hurt.

434
00:35:01,575 --> 00:35:03,205
I'm way more hurt than you are.

435
00:35:03,635 --> 00:35:04,645
About what?

436
00:35:05,605 --> 00:35:08,645
There's a difference between hiding things
and not expressing it.

437
00:35:08,945 --> 00:35:10,175
You're not expressing yourself?

438
00:35:10,785 --> 00:35:12,185
To me, of all people?

439
00:35:12,715 --> 00:35:14,045
The bold Geum Ba Ra?

440
00:35:14,955 --> 00:35:16,055
You think I'm bold?

441
00:35:17,185 --> 00:35:18,755
That's just how I come across.

442
00:35:20,685 --> 00:35:23,055
Never mind. I'm not upset.

443
00:35:24,165 --> 00:35:25,165
Really?

444
00:35:26,925 --> 00:35:28,935
If I hadn't come,
you'd have fallen asleep here, right?

445
00:35:29,265 --> 00:35:30,905
No, I have to shower before I can sleep.

446
00:35:31,465 --> 00:35:33,405
All right, I'll go then.
Go get cleaned up.

447
00:35:35,475 --> 00:35:36,675
But you said you were staying.

448
00:35:42,615 --> 00:35:45,045
Okay. Pickles and I will sleep out here.

449
00:35:46,315 --> 00:35:47,315
Pickles?

450
00:35:49,715 --> 00:35:52,385
Will you leave in a few hours
before the sun rises?

451
00:35:52,385 --> 00:35:55,455
Yes. It's a business meeting,
so I can't miss it.

452
00:35:59,195 --> 00:36:00,265
Don't you have any medication?

453
00:36:00,625 --> 00:36:01,635
No.

454
00:36:02,365 --> 00:36:06,735
Momo and I were catching up over drinks.
I don't want to sober up.

455
00:36:10,505 --> 00:36:12,575
You want to know what we talked about,
don't you?

456
00:36:17,315 --> 00:36:20,745
Stock the fridge with some food.
I'll come pick you up tomorrow evening.

457
00:36:21,215 --> 00:36:23,055
If things get tough, call me anytime.

458
00:37:12,465 --> 00:37:13,465
Isn't it pretty?

459
00:37:13,905 --> 00:37:15,205
Where'd you get it?

460
00:37:15,575 --> 00:37:16,835
Why does that matter?

461
00:37:17,235 --> 00:37:18,645
I bought it for you.

462
00:37:23,175 --> 00:37:24,175
Where'd you get the money?

463
00:37:24,585 --> 00:37:25,745
The woman sponsoring me.

464
00:37:26,445 --> 00:37:27,915
But she told me
to call her by her first name.

465
00:37:28,515 --> 00:37:29,515
You wear it.

466
00:37:30,255 --> 00:37:31,755
It looks prettier on you.

467
00:37:38,165 --> 00:37:40,225
I wish we could grow our hair out.

468
00:37:41,465 --> 00:37:43,865
The first thing I'll do
when I get out is grow my hair out.

469
00:37:44,665 --> 00:37:45,665
Me too.

470
00:37:48,605 --> 00:37:49,875
Oh, dear.

471
00:37:50,135 --> 00:37:52,775
Hey, do you know the song "Mom"?

472
00:37:54,045 --> 00:37:55,045
No.

473
00:37:55,815 --> 00:37:58,115
Last night, Su Bin...

474
00:37:58,845 --> 00:38:00,745
was crying while listening to that song.

475
00:38:03,115 --> 00:38:04,115
Mom.

476
00:38:05,725 --> 00:38:07,585
I wonder what it feels like
to call someone that.

477
00:38:13,965 --> 00:38:16,265
How about we close our eyes
and pretend to call for our moms?

478
00:38:16,665 --> 00:38:17,865
How?

479
00:38:18,965 --> 00:38:19,965
Just close them.

480
00:38:21,705 --> 00:38:23,635
I'll call out, and you answer me.

481
00:38:26,605 --> 00:38:27,675
Mom.

482
00:38:31,415 --> 00:38:32,415
Mom?

483
00:38:36,055 --> 00:38:37,085
Your turn.

484
00:38:40,325 --> 00:38:41,355
Come on.

485
00:38:43,325 --> 00:38:44,825
Mom.

486
00:38:46,025 --> 00:38:47,325
Why are you making your little sister cry?

487
00:38:48,365 --> 00:38:50,395
She's not my sister. We're friends.

488
00:38:50,535 --> 00:38:51,965
How old are you?

489
00:38:52,535 --> 00:38:53,565
Twelve.

490
00:38:53,865 --> 00:38:55,405
But she looks so little for her age.

491
00:38:56,075 --> 00:38:57,305
She's a picky eater.

492
00:38:57,535 --> 00:39:00,475
You must eat well to grow big and strong.
Don't be a picky eater.

493
00:39:01,075 --> 00:39:02,575
I'll buy you a treat.

494
00:39:03,315 --> 00:39:04,545
What a sweet friend.

495
00:39:06,445 --> 00:39:08,255
To think I treated her so well.

496
00:39:09,115 --> 00:39:10,615
And all she cares about is Momo.

497
00:39:15,755 --> 00:39:16,855
(Geum Ba Ra)

498
00:39:16,925 --> 00:39:18,695
Yong Joong, is now a good time to talk?

499
00:39:21,665 --> 00:39:22,665
Hello?

500
00:39:23,095 --> 00:39:24,195
Yong Joong.

501
00:39:24,965 --> 00:39:27,735
- Yes.
- Momo asked me to quit...

502
00:39:28,205 --> 00:39:29,835
and work for her.

503
00:39:31,605 --> 00:39:32,645
Really?

504
00:39:33,045 --> 00:39:34,305
But I'm not going to.

505
00:39:36,245 --> 00:39:37,645
That's the right call, right?

506
00:39:39,015 --> 00:39:40,585
You worked so hard to become a reporter.

507
00:39:42,585 --> 00:39:45,125
- Yes.
- I'm so proud of you.

508
00:39:46,385 --> 00:39:48,095
Is that why you adore me?

509
00:39:49,425 --> 00:39:50,455
Am I?

510
00:39:51,025 --> 00:39:52,325
Or was I just imagining it?

511
00:39:53,025 --> 00:39:54,495
We're in love.

512
00:39:55,195 --> 00:39:56,995
It's more than just being fond of you.

513
00:39:59,035 --> 00:40:02,405
Don't say things like that in public.
People won't understand.

514
00:40:02,675 --> 00:40:04,205
Does it matter what other people think?

515
00:40:05,545 --> 00:40:06,545
Bye.

516
00:40:07,405 --> 00:40:09,575
I love you. Sleep well.

517
00:40:10,145 --> 00:40:11,445
You too.

518
00:40:21,625 --> 00:40:24,595
I held on all this time
just for that tramp.

519
00:40:34,005 --> 00:40:36,135
You have no idea who I am.

520
00:40:48,715 --> 00:40:50,615
Send the van away. I'll take you.

521
00:41:15,675 --> 00:41:17,015
Your limit is three glasses of wine.

522
00:41:17,845 --> 00:41:18,945
Don't drink any more than that.

523
00:41:45,445 --> 00:41:46,745
Are you still uncomfortable around me?

524
00:42:02,195 --> 00:42:03,425
You look good in black.

525
00:42:06,095 --> 00:42:07,095
Are you on mute?

526
00:42:08,465 --> 00:42:09,465
Say something.

527
00:42:11,165 --> 00:42:13,765
Those two nurses who can't speak,

528
00:42:14,265 --> 00:42:15,305
what is their relationship?

529
00:42:16,775 --> 00:42:19,975
- Brother and sister?
- No. What makes you think that?

530
00:42:21,315 --> 00:42:22,545
They both ended up at the orphanage,

531
00:42:22,875 --> 00:42:25,185
and my dad found out
they were both in that state.

532
00:42:26,115 --> 00:42:27,545
He had us take special care
of them at our home.

533
00:42:29,815 --> 00:42:30,815
We basically raised them.

534
00:42:31,655 --> 00:42:34,485
Your father is such an admirable person.

535
00:42:35,055 --> 00:42:37,655
They've never forgotten his kindness.
They'll do anything I ask.

536
00:42:38,865 --> 00:42:40,095
As they should.

537
00:42:40,625 --> 00:42:41,995
How much can Geum Ba Ra drink?

538
00:42:44,495 --> 00:42:46,165
She had the same pairing as me today.

539
00:42:46,835 --> 00:42:48,105
And things like dining etiquette,

540
00:42:49,275 --> 00:42:50,275
did she learn them deliberately?

541
00:42:50,935 --> 00:42:52,475
From James.

542
00:42:53,605 --> 00:42:55,715
He often took her to
high-end restaurants, too.

543
00:42:56,145 --> 00:42:58,345
You have an appointment with Attorney Kim
on Monday at two.

544
00:42:59,615 --> 00:43:01,185
Review everything carefully
before you sign.

545
00:43:04,925 --> 00:43:06,655
It's a good thing your signature
is simple, at least.

546
00:43:16,465 --> 00:43:17,495
Darn it.

547
00:43:22,935 --> 00:43:24,375
She's not dead.

548
00:43:25,705 --> 00:43:26,975
You end your life,

549
00:43:27,575 --> 00:43:29,445
but you don't even leave
a single picture behind?

550
00:44:15,325 --> 00:44:17,755
My, it's beautiful.

551
00:44:18,665 --> 00:44:19,865
I haven't even tried it on yet.

552
00:44:28,335 --> 00:44:29,375
The smell of kimbap.

553
00:44:34,375 --> 00:44:37,315
The star is starving to death,
and you're wafting food smells everywhere.

554
00:44:38,415 --> 00:44:40,245
- I was so hungry...
- What about me?

555
00:44:40,585 --> 00:44:42,085
You had snacks earlier.

556
00:44:45,255 --> 00:44:46,385
Putting on a show for everyone?

557
00:44:51,465 --> 00:44:53,995
Your dark circles are terrible.
You didn't sleep again, did you?

558
00:44:54,195 --> 00:44:55,535
I was shooting a commercial until dawn.

559
00:44:55,935 --> 00:44:58,865
It's a good problem to have.
You really have it all.

560
00:44:59,605 --> 00:45:01,105
Everything except a Prince Charming.

561
00:45:01,805 --> 00:45:04,335
There are princes all over the world
just waiting for you to pick one.

562
00:45:05,305 --> 00:45:06,305
You didn't take the ice out.

563
00:45:07,975 --> 00:45:09,615
You know I only take
exactly three ice cubes.

564
00:45:11,015 --> 00:45:13,215
Seriously? You still don't know
after four months?

565
00:46:07,835 --> 00:46:08,835
Witch.

566
00:46:38,965 --> 00:46:41,005
Don't you ever think
Geum Ba Ra is a little too smart?

567
00:46:41,735 --> 00:46:43,975
What's wrong with being smart?

568
00:46:45,475 --> 00:46:46,745
That's because you
don't really know women.

569
00:46:47,745 --> 00:46:49,075
I guess not as well as you do.

570
00:46:49,975 --> 00:46:52,815
A person can't hide their character
or their aura.

571
00:46:53,615 --> 00:46:57,355
Besides, to me, Ba Ra isn't a woman.
She's like a kid sister.

572
00:46:57,685 --> 00:46:59,585
Do you think she feels the same way?

573
00:47:00,625 --> 00:47:02,325
I've known her since she was 11.

574
00:47:02,755 --> 00:47:03,825
Not consistently, you haven't.

575
00:47:04,195 --> 00:47:05,325
People don't change.

576
00:47:06,565 --> 00:47:07,965
They say you have to be reborn to do that.

577
00:47:08,895 --> 00:47:10,795
If that's the case,
then everyone has been reborn, right?

578
00:47:11,235 --> 00:47:12,805
But is everyone in the world
conscientious and kind?

579
00:47:14,565 --> 00:47:15,935
Remember what I told you
about the great monk?

580
00:47:17,175 --> 00:47:19,005
He said a person only changes
through spiritual training.

581
00:47:20,105 --> 00:47:24,075
Even if you're reincarnated 10,000 times,
you won't change without that training.

582
00:47:25,315 --> 00:47:27,015
Other than not having parents...

583
00:47:28,015 --> 00:47:30,655
Which isn't a flaw. It's not her fault.

584
00:47:32,825 --> 00:47:35,825
Her heart, her actions,
everything about her is proper.

585
00:47:36,395 --> 00:47:37,425
And the things she does are endearing.

586
00:47:39,765 --> 00:47:40,765
Anyway,

587
00:47:41,565 --> 00:47:43,665
I just hope I never have to call her
my sister-in-law.

588
00:47:43,965 --> 00:47:44,965
Don't worry.

589
00:47:45,505 --> 00:47:47,065
Either way, don't be so prejudiced
against people.

590
00:47:54,305 --> 00:47:55,715
- Good shot.
- Good shot.

591
00:47:56,075 --> 00:47:58,115
- Nice one.
- Good shot.

592
00:48:05,085 --> 00:48:06,955
- What's with this sudden rain?
- Quick, an umbrella, an umbrella!

593
00:48:06,955 --> 00:48:08,925
- Bring the umbrellas! Umbrellas!
- Was it supposed to be this bad?

594
00:48:09,795 --> 00:48:10,925
Hang on, take your swing again
under the umbrella.

595
00:48:10,995 --> 00:48:12,125
- It's raining so hard.
- Here's an umbrella.

596
00:48:43,195 --> 00:48:44,195
Goodness!

597
00:49:06,915 --> 00:49:07,915
Goodness!

598
00:49:27,735 --> 00:49:28,735
Geum Ba Ra.

599
00:49:29,335 --> 00:49:30,335
Pickles.

600
00:49:34,305 --> 00:49:35,475
(Yong Joong)

601
00:49:37,415 --> 00:49:38,645
(Yong Joong)

602
00:49:42,055 --> 00:49:43,555
The person you have called is unavailable.

603
00:49:43,555 --> 00:49:44,555
Please leave a message after...

604
00:50:07,575 --> 00:50:08,575
Goodness!

605
00:50:27,365 --> 00:50:28,365
I thought you'd be here.

606
00:50:31,235 --> 00:50:34,305
I thought you two came together.

607
00:50:35,405 --> 00:50:37,335
It was pouring, so we cut our game short.

608
00:50:37,905 --> 00:50:40,045
Your scream startled me
more than the thunder.

609
00:50:40,545 --> 00:50:43,415
I'm actually a little afraid of the rain.

610
00:50:45,245 --> 00:50:46,245
You're afraid of the rain?

611
00:50:47,215 --> 00:50:48,215
Yes.

612
00:50:51,055 --> 00:50:53,125
- What can I get you?
- Sparkling water.

613
00:50:53,885 --> 00:50:54,885
I'll have the same.

614
00:50:57,095 --> 00:50:59,495
I came to make you jjajangmyeon. Surprise!

615
00:51:03,335 --> 00:51:04,335
Where's Pickles?

616
00:51:04,735 --> 00:51:05,735
In the living room.

617
00:51:06,235 --> 00:51:07,235
He's not here.

618
00:51:07,735 --> 00:51:09,505
- Pickles.
- Pickles!

619
00:51:09,575 --> 00:51:10,575
Pickles!

620
00:51:11,075 --> 00:51:13,045
- Pickles!
- Pickles.

621
00:51:21,015 --> 00:51:22,015
Pickles!

622
00:51:27,625 --> 00:51:28,625
Goodness.

623
00:51:32,125 --> 00:51:33,495
Dogs get scared of thunder.

624
00:51:33,895 --> 00:51:35,135
Oh, Carrie?

625
00:51:36,265 --> 00:51:38,135
That chihuahua James used to have.

626
00:51:39,005 --> 00:51:40,965
- Her name was Oiji, right?
- Yes.

627
00:51:41,465 --> 00:51:42,475
Aren't you hungry?

628
00:51:42,905 --> 00:51:43,905
Starving.

629
00:51:44,375 --> 00:51:46,545
- You should eat with us.
- Drop the formalities.

630
00:51:46,745 --> 00:51:47,775
We're friends.

631
00:51:49,575 --> 00:51:51,475
Just give me a minute.
I just need to stir-fry it up.

632
00:51:52,085 --> 00:51:53,845
- Anything I can do to help?
- No, I'm good.

633
00:51:56,655 --> 00:51:58,015
Just hire a live-in housekeeper.

634
00:51:58,355 --> 00:51:59,355
That'd make me uncomfortable.

635
00:52:01,525 --> 00:52:02,525
Here.

636
00:52:04,325 --> 00:52:05,995
A friend of my dad's
runs a traditional medicine clinic.

637
00:52:06,925 --> 00:52:10,095
He made this with his best ingredients
before passing the practice on to his son.

638
00:52:10,595 --> 00:52:11,795
I don't take herbal medicine.

639
00:52:12,105 --> 00:52:14,605
Still, he went to the trouble
of having it made for you.

640
00:52:15,135 --> 00:52:17,275
- I don't need a health tonic.
- What, and you think I do?

641
00:52:17,335 --> 00:52:18,335
Just take it.

642
00:52:18,845 --> 00:52:21,105
It's got deer antler, agarwood, and musk.
All the best ingredients.

643
00:52:21,245 --> 00:52:22,845
You said you liked this watch, right?

644
00:52:23,115 --> 00:52:24,275
I bought one too.

645
00:52:24,745 --> 00:52:25,785
How'd you get your hands on one?

646
00:52:26,115 --> 00:52:28,485
If I want something, I get it.
You managed to get one, after all.

647
00:52:28,555 --> 00:52:29,715
(Let the Duel Begin)

648
00:53:33,145 --> 00:53:35,315
- That smells incredible.
- It's ready!

649
00:53:35,615 --> 00:53:36,655
This is the real deal.

650
00:53:36,955 --> 00:53:37,955
No guarantees on the taste, though.

651
00:53:48,125 --> 00:53:49,165
The rain stopped.

652
00:53:49,595 --> 00:53:50,695
It was coming down so hard too.

653
00:53:52,505 --> 00:53:53,705
You did all this by yourself?
That's a lot of work.

654
00:53:54,135 --> 00:53:55,135
It was nothing.

655
00:53:59,445 --> 00:54:01,745
This is so much better than the hotel's.
It's not too sweet.

656
00:54:02,915 --> 00:54:04,645
Pickles, go eat your own food.

657
00:54:05,745 --> 00:54:08,385
Is this a recipe you found online?
Or did a chef teach you?

658
00:54:08,655 --> 00:54:10,785
It's my own recipe, just how I like it.

659
00:54:10,785 --> 00:54:11,985
A Geum Ba Ra original?

660
00:54:13,285 --> 00:54:15,155
I wanted to thank you properly
for everything.

661
00:54:15,795 --> 00:54:16,855
It's just a humble meal.

662
00:54:17,125 --> 00:54:20,765
- Repay me for what?
- For that fancy, belated birthday dinner.

663
00:54:21,225 --> 00:54:22,435
Did I cook it myself?

664
00:54:22,565 --> 00:54:25,865
Even if the housekeeper made it,
the thought counts.

665
00:54:27,605 --> 00:54:29,505
Can a woman take this tonic?

666
00:54:30,575 --> 00:54:31,875
He said it was formulated for men.

667
00:54:32,875 --> 00:54:34,645
I'll open a Chinese restaurant for you.

668
00:54:38,745 --> 00:54:39,815
Hello?

669
00:54:40,385 --> 00:54:44,915
- James. Hi.
- Do you think I could get an MRI?

670
00:54:45,485 --> 00:54:47,325
Why? Are you feeling unwell?

671
00:54:47,325 --> 00:54:48,555
I've been feeling a little dizzy.

672
00:54:48,825 --> 00:54:49,825
Is it bad?

673
00:54:50,225 --> 00:54:52,565
- How bad?
- It's not too bad.

674
00:54:52,865 --> 00:54:54,495
And I had a bit of a headache
the day before yesterday.

675
00:54:54,795 --> 00:54:56,695
We're fully booked,
so squeezing you in is tough.

676
00:54:57,265 --> 00:54:59,235
I can do it early in the morning
or late at night.

677
00:54:59,465 --> 00:55:01,405
Morning's best, even if it's early.

678
00:55:01,405 --> 00:55:03,305
Okay, I'll check and send you a text.

679
00:55:03,605 --> 00:55:04,605
Thank you.

680
00:55:06,845 --> 00:55:08,105
I'm sure it's nothing serious.

681
00:55:08,775 --> 00:55:10,545
If he had a burst blood vessel
or was having a stroke,

682
00:55:10,975 --> 00:55:12,015
the headache would be extremely severe.

683
00:55:13,115 --> 00:55:14,645
My brother's a bit of a hypochondriac.

684
00:55:14,845 --> 00:55:16,015
That's a good thing, though.

685
00:55:18,655 --> 00:55:21,185
- A cocktail?
- Not quite a cocktail.

686
00:55:29,635 --> 00:55:30,635
There's wine in here.

687
00:55:31,135 --> 00:55:32,435
Wine and two other things.

688
00:55:32,705 --> 00:55:33,705
This is pretty good.

689
00:55:35,335 --> 00:55:38,435
Without the housekeeper,
I figured you'd be alone.

690
00:55:38,435 --> 00:55:40,575
I felt bad, so I came by to surprise you.
Was it okay?

691
00:55:40,645 --> 00:55:42,615
It was perfect. Thank you.

692
00:55:43,345 --> 00:55:44,415
If you're not drinking that, give it here.

693
00:55:48,215 --> 00:55:49,855
You'll get drunk drinking that fast.

694
00:55:49,915 --> 00:55:51,215
Getting drunk is for girls.

695
00:55:52,055 --> 00:55:53,525
You don't have to force yourself
to drink it.

696
00:55:53,585 --> 00:55:54,585
If you don't like it.

697
00:55:58,325 --> 00:55:59,325
Just leave the dishes.

698
00:56:00,025 --> 00:56:01,095
I already put them in the dishwasher.

699
00:56:01,795 --> 00:56:02,795
Let's go to the grocery store.

700
00:56:06,705 --> 00:56:07,965
(Manager, Nua Children's Home)

701
00:56:12,205 --> 00:56:14,075
- It's me.
- Director.

702
00:56:14,145 --> 00:56:15,715
Please email me Geum Ba Ra's file.

703
00:56:16,175 --> 00:56:18,415
- Everything you have on her.
- Understood.

704
00:57:13,965 --> 00:57:16,535
We'll run the scan,
but I'm sure it's nothing.

705
00:57:16,605 --> 00:57:18,135
That would be a relief.

706
00:57:19,675 --> 00:57:21,045
Take this after your scan.

707
00:57:21,805 --> 00:57:23,315
- Herbal medicine?
- Yes.

708
00:57:23,575 --> 00:57:25,585
I gave Yong Joong some too.
So enjoy all of it to yourself.

709
00:57:26,015 --> 00:57:29,115
I'll enjoy it.
How did you know I love this stuff?

710
00:57:29,585 --> 00:57:32,825
Sorry to make such a fuss
on your rare day off.

711
00:57:32,885 --> 00:57:34,585
You personally came on a house call.

712
00:57:39,165 --> 00:57:41,965
(Hope and Happiness Pharmacy)

713
00:57:45,295 --> 00:57:46,305
Hi, how can I help you?

714
00:57:46,835 --> 00:57:47,835
A pregnancy test, please.

715
00:57:54,105 --> 00:57:55,105
That's five dollars.

716
00:58:08,185 --> 00:58:10,595
What was up with Ju Shin
in the kitchen earlier?

717
00:58:12,125 --> 00:58:14,495
My scream probably startled him
into doing something out of character.

718
00:58:14,925 --> 00:58:16,795
He's probably kicking himself for it now.

719
00:58:18,735 --> 00:58:21,505
I was the one who freaked out.
I thought it was you.

720
00:58:21,765 --> 00:58:22,975
Are you that scared of rain?

721
00:58:23,505 --> 00:58:24,705
This kind of rain, yes.

722
00:58:25,235 --> 00:58:26,545
Especially with the thunder and lightning.

723
00:58:27,475 --> 00:58:28,875
So what do you do when you're alone?

724
00:58:29,945 --> 00:58:31,045
I just deal with it.

725
00:58:31,845 --> 00:58:33,385
That can't be good for your heart.

726
00:58:34,185 --> 00:58:36,255
Shouldn't you go check on James?

727
00:58:36,555 --> 00:58:38,615
I'll stop by after I drop you off.

728
00:58:39,485 --> 00:58:40,655
Yong Joong.

729
00:58:40,955 --> 00:58:45,055
James told me to call him my big brother,
but I can't bring myself to say it.

730
00:58:47,625 --> 00:58:48,725
Then don't force it.

731
00:58:50,435 --> 00:58:52,935
Besides me, even Ju Shin...

732
00:58:53,435 --> 00:58:56,105
Of course not.
The Director wouldn't allow it.

733
00:58:57,005 --> 00:58:59,645
All the kids at the orphanage
adored the Director.

734
00:59:00,275 --> 00:59:01,275
Especially Jin Ju.

735
00:59:02,415 --> 00:59:04,615
He had this incredible aura about him.

736
00:59:04,615 --> 00:59:05,645
Ju Shin?

737
00:59:05,645 --> 00:59:06,685
Yes.

738
00:59:09,885 --> 00:59:10,885
What about me?

739
00:59:12,455 --> 00:59:14,655
You're all warmth and charm.

740
00:59:15,225 --> 00:59:16,825
Aura versus warmth.

741
00:59:18,425 --> 00:59:20,425
People are more drawn to that human side.

742
00:59:20,965 --> 00:59:21,965
At least, I am.

743
00:59:23,895 --> 00:59:26,205
Pickles will be waiting.
Let's pack this up to go.

744
00:59:27,035 --> 00:59:29,675
You can make amazing black bean noodles,

745
00:59:30,475 --> 00:59:31,875
but you keep your fridge totally empty.

746
00:59:33,445 --> 00:59:34,505
Thank you. I'll really enjoy this.

747
00:59:40,715 --> 00:59:41,715
Pickles, let's go.

748
00:59:52,225 --> 00:59:54,565
(Student's detailed school record,
Student Record 2)

749
00:59:54,625 --> 00:59:56,035
(Name: Geum Ba Ra)

750
00:59:58,695 --> 01:00:04,935
(Awards, Awarding institution:
Principal of Minjin Elementary School)

751
01:00:08,175 --> 01:00:09,175
I'm sorry.

752
01:00:13,545 --> 01:00:15,245
Considering your future,

753
01:00:16,185 --> 01:00:18,615
we've agreed to tell everyone
that you're annulling the adoption.

754
01:00:19,825 --> 01:00:21,025
Don't let on, though.

755
01:00:21,425 --> 01:00:23,455
I'll tell the Office Manager the truth...

756
01:00:24,095 --> 01:00:25,425
and clear your name.

757
01:00:43,145 --> 01:00:44,275
Hey, Yong Joong.

758
01:00:44,275 --> 01:00:46,815
I love how you always answer right away.

759
01:00:47,715 --> 01:00:51,015
It's weird. You only ever seem to call
when I'm free to answer.

760
01:00:51,715 --> 01:00:52,755
Can you video chat?

761
01:00:53,255 --> 01:00:54,255
Yes.

762
01:00:57,925 --> 01:00:59,825
- Call for him.
- Pickles!

763
01:00:59,925 --> 01:01:02,535
Where's that sound coming from?
Where is she?

764
01:01:04,095 --> 01:01:06,835
- He's not interested.
- Pickles looks drained.

765
01:01:07,205 --> 01:01:08,205
I played with him for a while.

766
01:01:08,465 --> 01:01:10,575
You can't just think of your own stamina.

767
01:01:10,575 --> 01:01:12,975
He's 9kg, and you're over 70, right?

768
01:01:13,045 --> 01:01:14,045
I'm 75kg.

769
01:01:14,375 --> 01:01:15,375
How is that even a fair match?

770
01:01:15,915 --> 01:01:17,915
Have you showered yet? Are you done?

771
01:01:18,375 --> 01:01:19,385
I was about to.

772
01:01:19,745 --> 01:01:21,115
I've seen it all, so what's there to hide?

773
01:01:21,385 --> 01:01:22,415
You look pretty.

774
01:01:22,615 --> 01:01:24,355
One of your many great qualities...

775
01:01:24,755 --> 01:01:25,955
is giving unconditional compliments.

776
01:01:25,955 --> 01:01:27,455
I'm just telling the truth.

777
01:01:28,785 --> 01:01:30,555
- Hey!
- What?

778
01:01:30,555 --> 01:01:32,025
He's peeing while staring right at me.

779
01:01:33,525 --> 01:01:34,525
Are you jealous?

780
01:01:35,095 --> 01:01:36,635
- I'm hanging up.
- Okay.

781
01:01:39,065 --> 01:01:40,365
Who's that this late?

782
01:01:40,365 --> 01:01:42,235
I don't know. Let me call you back.

783
01:01:42,235 --> 01:01:43,735
- No, don't hang up.
- Okay.

784
01:01:48,245 --> 01:01:50,245
It's Momo. I'm hanging up.

785
01:01:50,775 --> 01:01:51,775
Okay.

786
01:02:03,225 --> 01:02:04,755
I didn't come here to be turned down.

787
01:02:10,095 --> 01:02:12,395
Wouldn't it be better to just hire
another assistant instead of me?

788
01:02:12,465 --> 01:02:14,565
What if they leak my private life online?

789
01:02:16,235 --> 01:02:18,135
How can you trust someone
without getting to know them first?

790
01:02:22,575 --> 01:02:23,675
Who were you drinking with?

791
01:02:27,115 --> 01:02:28,315
You're the only one...

792
01:02:28,785 --> 01:02:31,515
I can trust and rely on now.

793
01:02:44,995 --> 01:02:46,165
(Pregnancy Test)

794
01:02:49,005 --> 01:02:50,275
(Fast, easy, and 99 percent accurate)

795
01:03:06,525 --> 01:03:08,525
- Hello?
- Is the party over?

796
01:03:09,595 --> 01:03:11,325
Yes, I just got home.

797
01:03:11,325 --> 01:03:13,065
Nurse Park will be there in 20 minutes.

798
01:03:13,525 --> 01:03:14,525
Get a ride with him.

799
01:03:30,415 --> 01:03:31,845
Where are we going?

800
01:04:11,515 --> 01:04:12,515
Did you have fun?

801
01:04:13,925 --> 01:04:14,925
It was fine.

802
01:04:18,295 --> 01:04:19,295
It's from the garden.

803
01:04:30,035 --> 01:04:31,605
When are you going to stop
that lip-licking habit?

804
01:04:34,405 --> 01:04:36,775
Right away. Never again.

805
01:05:53,955 --> 01:05:56,095
I can't let a senior
go to the hospital alone.

806
01:06:02,695 --> 01:06:06,665
A lady once said a young guy
was giving her an attitude.

807
01:06:06,965 --> 01:06:09,305
So she went, "I've been young before.
I know what youth is."

808
01:06:09,635 --> 01:06:10,635
"But have you ever been old?"

809
01:06:10,975 --> 01:06:12,135
"I have."

810
01:06:12,135 --> 01:06:13,945
"So don't act so high and mighty
when you don't know a thing about aging."

811
01:06:14,545 --> 01:06:16,675
The fact that you’re hurt shows
you've really gotten old.

812
01:06:16,875 --> 01:06:17,975
Why, you little...

813
01:06:28,485 --> 01:06:30,755
(Department of Radiology)

814
01:06:53,245 --> 01:06:54,615
What are your thoughts on a brain swap?

815
01:06:58,215 --> 01:06:59,355
Have you ever thought about it?

816
01:07:01,685 --> 01:07:02,685
No, I haven't.

817
01:07:03,955 --> 01:07:08,025
I heard that soon, AI will be able
to transplant entire human heads.

818
01:07:11,935 --> 01:07:13,065
What if it were possible...

819
01:07:14,265 --> 01:07:16,005
to swap only the brain
without changing the face?

820
01:07:24,645 --> 01:07:25,645
By any chance,

821
01:07:27,345 --> 01:07:28,385
are you talking about you, Director?

822
01:07:45,165 --> 01:07:46,365
If it were possible,

823
01:07:49,235 --> 01:07:50,235
who would I swap with?

824
01:08:34,545 --> 01:08:37,215
(Doctor Shin)

825
01:08:37,315 --> 01:08:40,085
- Goodness. Congratulations!
- Congratulations?

826
01:08:40,155 --> 01:08:41,425
What if it were possible...

827
01:08:41,425 --> 01:08:43,425
to swap only the brain
without changing the face?

828
01:08:43,725 --> 01:08:45,925
By any chance,
are you talking about you, Director?

829
01:08:45,925 --> 01:08:46,925
Do you trust people?

830
01:08:46,995 --> 01:08:49,765
I have to, at first.
But I never want to be betrayed.

831
01:08:49,765 --> 01:08:50,895
What if they do?

832
01:08:50,895 --> 01:08:52,135
What's your relationship to her?

833
01:08:52,195 --> 01:08:54,835
- I'm her father.
- I hold all the cards now, don't I?

834
01:08:54,935 --> 01:08:56,005
Have I lost it all now?

835
01:08:56,535 --> 01:08:57,935
You even talk like that?

836
01:08:58,075 --> 01:08:59,105
Don't change the subject.

837
01:08:59,105 --> 01:09:00,245
What's your type?

838
01:09:00,245 --> 01:09:01,845
- Time to go.
- Can't I stay?

839
01:09:01,845 --> 01:09:03,315
I know you're just saying that.

840
01:09:03,375 --> 01:09:04,515
I'm not just saying that.

841
01:09:05,945 --> 01:09:07,915
How dare you lie to me?

842
01:09:08,585 --> 01:09:09,585
Lie?

843
01:09:10,555 --> 01:09:11,585
Why would I?

844
01:09:11,655 --> 01:09:13,155
How can you enjoy strawberries right now?

845
01:09:13,825 --> 01:09:14,825
Like nothing's wrong?

846
01:09:14,885 --> 01:09:18,455
Yes. I must be low on Vitamin C
because they're delicious.

847
01:09:19,765 --> 01:09:21,765
Give me back my brain!

848
01:09:22,095 --> 01:09:23,535
- Director!
- Please, help us!

849
01:09:23,865 --> 01:09:26,435
Shin Ju Shin, you're under arrest
for the murder of Kim Jin Ju.

850
01:09:29,265 --> 01:09:31,275
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
